# STRATEGICLAND — Narrative Density System

> Cinema is **rhythm**, not intensity.
> A film that is "epic" for 90 minutes is **exhausting**, not memorable.
> The most cinematic moments live in the **silence after the climax**, not in the climax itself.
> The page must **modulate** — between weight and weightlessness, density and air.

---

## 1. Density Philosophy

- The project's signature is not its peaks — it is its **valleys**. Without silence, the peaks have no meaning.
- Every chapter occupies one or more **density tiers**. No chapter is "constantly cinematic".
- Density modulation operates at three scales:
  - **Scene** (within a chapter)
  - **Chapter** (within a page)
  - **Page** (within a session)
- The audience must experience **at least one** TIER 01 (silence) and **at most one** TIER 05 (kinetic) per page.

This rule **governs** the composition of `chapter-architecture.mdc` and the orchestration of `motion-system.mdc`, `atmosphere-system.mdc`, `webgl-system.mdc`, `image-treatment-system.mdc`. It is the **conductor's score**.

---

## 2. Density Tiers (LOCKED)

Five canonical tiers. **Never** invent intermediates. Each tier specifies a complete envelope.

### TIER 01 — SILENCE
| Aspect                  | Value                                              |
|-------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Motion intensity        | None on entry; only ambient atmosphere drift       |
| Typography density      | ≤ 8 words on screen, single block                  |
| Type scale              | `type.body` or `type.caption` only                 |
| Image frequency         | 0 images, or 1 image at ≤ 30% viewport width       |
| Atmospheric complexity  | Grain only; vignette at minimum chapter intensity  |
| WebGL                   | Disabled or paused (uniforms frozen)               |
| Transition speed in/out | `DUR.epic` (1.8s) — long, slow, deliberate         |
| Hover affordances       | 0                                                  |
| Scroll height           | ≥ 60vh (≥ 50vh mobile)                             |
| Emotional pressure      | 0/10 — **rest**                                    |

### TIER 02 — CONTEMPLATIVE
| Aspect                  | Value                                              |
|-------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Motion intensity        | Single reveal, `DUR.cinematic`+, blur entry        |
| Typography density      | ≤ 30 words; single editorial block                 |
| Type scale              | `type.lede` or `type.title`                        |
| Image frequency         | 0–1 image, deliberately framed                     |
| Atmospheric complexity  | Grain + vignette + light leak (low)                |
| WebGL                   | Optional, ambient only (lowest amplitude)          |
| Transition speed in/out | `DUR.cinematic` (1.2s)                             |
| Hover affordances       | ≤ 1                                                |
| Scroll height           | 80–120vh                                           |
| Emotional pressure      | 2/10 — **breathing**                               |

### TIER 03 — EDITORIAL
| Aspect                  | Value                                              |
|-------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Motion intensity        | 2–3 reveal clusters, staggered                     |
| Typography density      | 30–120 words; eyebrow + display + lede + body      |
| Type scale              | `type.headline`/`type.display` + body              |
| Image frequency         | 1–2 images, paired with copy                       |
| Atmospheric complexity  | Full chapter atmosphere (grain + vignette + tint)  |
| WebGL                   | Optional ambient                                   |
| Transition speed in/out | `DUR.standard` (720ms)                             |
| Hover affordances       | ≤ 2                                                |
| Scroll height           | 100–150vh                                          |
| Emotional pressure      | 4/10 — **engaged**                                 |

### TIER 04 — IMMERSIVE
| Aspect                  | Value                                              |
|-------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Motion intensity        | Layered reveals (atmospheric + structural + detail) |
| Typography density      | Display title dominant; minimal body               |
| Type scale              | `type.display` or `type.epic`                      |
| Image frequency         | 1 hero image full-bleed, or 0 (WebGL dominant)     |
| Atmospheric complexity  | Full chapter atmosphere + WebGL + light leak peak  |
| WebGL                   | Active, mid-amplitude                              |
| Transition speed in/out | `DUR.epic` (1.8s) into, `DUR.cinematic` out        |
| Hover affordances       | ≤ 1 (ideally 0)                                    |
| Scroll height           | 120–200vh                                          |
| Emotional pressure      | 7/10 — **enveloped**                               |

### TIER 05 — KINETIC
| Aspect                  | Value                                              |
|-------------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Motion intensity        | Pinned + scrubbed timeline; multi-layer parallax   |
| Typography density      | Mixed: large + small, multiple beats               |
| Type scale              | `type.display` + `type.caption` simultaneously     |
| Image frequency         | 3–6 images sequenced (case study horizontal)       |
| Atmospheric complexity  | Full + atmospheric reactions to scroll velocity    |
| WebGL                   | Optional, peak amplitude                           |
| Transition speed in/out | `DUR.epic` in, `DUR.epic` out — heavy weight      |
| Hover affordances       | ≤ 3                                                |
| Scroll height           | 200–300vh (pinned)                                 |
| Emotional pressure      | 9/10 — **compression**                             |

### Density token
```ts
// lib/density/types.ts
export type DensityTier = "T01_SILENCE" | "T02_CONTEMPLATIVE" | "T03_EDITORIAL" | "T04_IMMERSIVE" | "T05_KINETIC";

export const TIER = {
  silence:       "T01_SILENCE",
  contemplative: "T02_CONTEMPLATIVE",
  editorial:     "T03_EDITORIAL",
  immersive:     "T04_IMMERSIVE",
  kinetic:       "T05_KINETIC",
} as const;
```

Every `<SceneShell>` declares its `tier`. The shell enforces tier constraints (motion budget, hover affordance count, atmosphere config) at runtime in dev mode.

