## 3. Chapter Density Mapping

Each canonical chapter type (per `chapter-architecture.mdc`) declares an **allowed tier set** and a **default sequence**.

| Chapter type | Allowed tiers                          | Default scene tier sequence                                |
|--------------|----------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| `hero`       | T02, T04                               | T04 (establishing) → T02 (lede hold) → T01 (scroll cue)    |
| `editorial`  | T01, T02, T03                          | T02 → T03 → T03 → T01 → T02                                |
| `case`       | T03, T04, T05                          | T03 (intro) → T04 (frame) → T05 (pinned) → T04 (release) → T02 (caption hold) |
| `human`      | T01, T02                               | T02 → T01 → T02 → T01                                      |
| `cultural`   | T01, T03, T04, T05                     | T03 → T04 → T05 (climax) → T01 (silence) → T03 (resolution)|
| `closing`    | T01, T02                               | T02 → T01 → T01                                            |

### Constraints
- A chapter must contain **at least one TIER 01 scene** if its allowed tier set includes T01.
- `case` chapters **must** end on T02 (cooldown), never on T05 (compression with no release).
- `cultural` chapters are the **only** chapters allowed to traverse 4 different tiers in one chapter.
- `human` and `closing` chapters are **forbidden** from using T03+. They are the **rest** of the page.

