## 8. Scene Energy System

Each scene declares a **scene energy class**. A chapter's scene energy distribution must follow its chapter type's profile.

| Energy class    | Tier     | Characteristics                                          |
|-----------------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| **Low energy**  | T01      | Stillness; the eye rests                                 |
| **Suspended**   | T01–T02  | Held breath; one visible element, slow drift             |
| **Tension**     | T03–T04  | Build; reveals stack; the atmosphere thickens            |
| **Release**     | T02      | Breath out; type-only; minimal reveal                    |
| **Immersive**   | T04      | Enveloping; WebGL or full-bleed image; layered motion    |
| **Contemplative**| T02     | Reading; lede + body; one image                          |
| **Climactic**   | T05      | Compression; pinned; atmosphere at peak                  |

Distribution requirement per chapter:
- A chapter must include **at least 2 distinct energy classes**.
- A chapter that ends on **Tension** without a **Release** is malformed.

