## 9. Composition API

```tsx
// In a chapter component
import { Tier } from "@lib/density";

export function CulturalChapter() {
  return (
    <ChapterShell chapter={culturalAtmosphere}>
      <SceneShell tier={Tier.editorial} energy="contemplative">
        <Eyebrow>003 — DRIFT</Eyebrow>
        <DisplayTitle>The shape of stillness.</DisplayTitle>
      </SceneShell>

      <SceneShell tier={Tier.immersive} energy="immersive">
        <HeroImage src="..." reveal="blur" />
      </SceneShell>

      <SceneShell tier={Tier.kinetic} energy="climactic" pin>
        <PinnedHorizontalSequence slides={...} />
      </SceneShell>

      <SceneShell tier={Tier.silence} energy="suspended" minHeight="80vh">
        {/* intentionally empty — this is the silence */}
      </SceneShell>

      <SceneShell tier={Tier.editorial} energy="release">
        <EditorialBlock>...</EditorialBlock>
      </SceneShell>
    </ChapterShell>
  );
}
```

The `<SceneShell>` reads `tier` and `energy` and:
- Enforces motion budget (max reveals per tier).
- Enforces hover affordance count.
- Configures atmosphere intensity multipliers.
- Configures the chapter's atmosphere shader uniforms (`uIntensity` driven by tier number).
- Calls into `lintPage()` in dev mode.

